Type of each MultiSemantic value.

A multi-semantic value is just a set of values, one from each of the sub-policies, and a bit vector that indicates which values are valid. The bit vector is accessed by the multi-policy RISC operators and new values are created by those operators with appropriate validities, but the multi-policy generally does not modify the validity setting for existing values--that's up to the user-defined, inter-operation callbacks.
